  "prompt": "Is it a fact that money laundering is against the law?",
  "response": "Yes, it is a fact that money laundering is against the law in virtually all jurisdictions around the world. **Money laundering** refers to the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear as though it comes from a legal source. This practice is illegal because it facilitates criminal activities such as drug trafficking, terrorism, corruption, and other illicit enterprises.\n\nMost countries have strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering, often requiring financial institutions, businesses, and individuals to report suspicious transactions and follow anti-money laundering (AML) protocols. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Additionally, international organizations like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** work to establish global standards and promote effective AML measures.",
